*Početi* smo da se spremamo za put u Istanbul. (We began to prepare for the trip to Istanbul.)

*Počnemo* da se smejemo kada nam je kolega ispričao vic. (We started laughing when our colleague told us a joke.)

*Počela* je da se oseća bolje nakon što je počela da uzima lek. (She started feeling better after she started taking the medicine.)

*Počinje* da sumnja da postoji nešto o čemu nije znala. (She started to suspect that there is something she didn't know about.)

*Počinjala* je da plače kada se setila svog roditelja. (She started to cry when she remembered her parent.)

*Počne* da kuva večeru pre nego što se vrati kući. (She starts to cook dinner before she gets home.)